SeldonFrame coding rules

Execution model
- Complete one planned step at a time.
- After each step: run `pnpm build` and stop for confirmation.
- Do not batch future roadmap steps.

Current monorepo layout
- Apps: `apps/web`, `apps/cloud`, `apps/pro`
- Packages: `packages/core`, `packages/crm`, `packages/payments`

Package boundaries
- `@seldonframe/core`: shared primitives only (integrations, events, telemetry, virality)
- `@seldonframe/crm`: product behavior, routes, server actions, UI composition
- `@seldonframe/payments`: payment-specific logic

Current key paths
- CRM routes: `packages/crm/src/app/(dashboard)`
- CRM API: `packages/crm/src/app/api/v1`
- Domain actions: `packages/crm/src/lib/*/actions.ts`
- Schema: `packages/crm/src/db/schema`
- Soul: `packages/crm/src/lib/soul`, `packages/crm/src/components/soul`
- Layout shell: `packages/crm/src/components/layout`

Current design system
- Glass cards: `glass-card`
- Premium typography hierarchy (`text-page-title`, card/section title tokens)
- Sidebar glow/active state styling in `packages/crm/src/styles/components/overrides.css`

Recent CRM components/features
- Inline contacts table editing:
  - `packages/crm/src/components/contacts/contacts-inline-table.tsx`
  - `packages/crm/src/lib/contacts/actions.ts` (`updateContactFieldAction`)
- Split contact detail layout + inline custom field formatting:
  - `packages/crm/src/app/(dashboard)/contacts/[id]/page.tsx`
- Deep command palette search:
  - `packages/crm/src/components/layout/command-palette.tsx`
  - `packages/crm/src/app/(dashboard)/layout.tsx`
- Booking availability/timezone/calendar sync:
  - `packages/crm/src/components/bookings/bookings-page-content.tsx`
  - `packages/crm/src/components/bookings/public-booking-form.tsx`
  - `packages/crm/src/lib/bookings/actions.ts`
  - `packages/crm/src/lib/bookings/google-calendar-sync.ts`

UI skill location
- Local clone: `ui-ux-pro-max-skill/`

Safety
- No destructive git commands.
- No hardcoded credentials.
- No logging of secrets.
- Respect demo read-only guards on write paths.

Platform constraints
- Next.js 16 conventions may differ from legacy patterns.
- Read docs in `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before changing framework behavior.

Verification
- Build from root: `pnpm build`.
- If build fails, fix only errors introduced by the current step.

## Block Architecture

SeldonFrame has two types of blocks:

### Built-in blocks
- Located in `packages/crm/src/app/(dashboard)/[blockName]/`
- Follow these patterns:
  - Schema in `packages/crm/src/db/schema.ts`
  - Server actions in `packages/crm/src/lib/[blockName]/actions.ts`
  - Page components in `packages/crm/src/app/(dashboard)/[blockName]/page.tsx`
  - Detail pages in `packages/crm/src/app/(dashboard)/[blockName]/[id]/page.tsx`
  - Public pages in `packages/crm/src/app/[publicRoute]/page.tsx`

### Marketplace blocks
- Defined by BLOCK.md specs (see `BLOCK_MD_SPEC.md`)
- When implementing a BLOCK.md:
  - Create schema following existing Drizzle patterns (`orgId` on every table, UUID primary keys)
  - Create server actions following existing patterns (`"use server"`, `revalidatePath`)
  - Create pages following existing patterns (`useSoulLabels()`, `glass-card`)
  - Emit events using `emitEvent()` from `@seldonframe/core`
  - Read soul via `getSoul(orgId)` or `useSoulLabels()`
  - Map BLOCK.md `Person` to contacts (`contactId` FK)
  - Map BLOCK.md `Identity` to soul config
  - Map BLOCK.md `Payments` to Stripe Connect (`org.stripeAccountId`)
  - Map BLOCK.md `Email` to existing email actions
  - Register in built-in registry or marketplace tables based on block type
